Code: datashader.py

This datashader plot is about global active power consumption measured by each minute from 2017 to 2011.

We can see from the plot that global active power consumption has a seasonal pattern, for example, it reaches the highest value in January each year.

Also, it reaches the extreme lowest value in September, 2018.

Code: a6-d3.R

This d3 plot is about daily global active power consumption measured by each day from 2007 to 2011.

We can see from the plot that daily global active power consumption fluctuates dramatically but the extreme highest value is decreasing as time goes by.

Moreover, it also shows clearly that global active power consumption has a seasonal pattern as the same with the plot above.
